steps.instruction:
1. Chop the thyme 
2. Zest the orange
3. Squeeze 1/3 cup of juice from the orange 
4. Cut pork into 3/4" thick slices
5. Wash hands
6. Place porn into plastic bag
7. Add marinade, pepper, thyme, and zest 
8. Let sit for 10 minutes (up to overnight)
9. Preheat large sauté pan on medium-high heat (2 to 3 minutes)
10. Put the butter on the pan 
11. Once the butter is melted add the pork
12. Cook for 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until the middle registers 145F
13. Measure the remaining ingredients and arrange near the stove top
14. Remove pork from pan
15. Reduce heat to medium and add garlic
16. Cook for 1 minute
17. Stir in flour, cook and stir for 1 to 2 minutes or until the mixture begins to brown
18. Add the green onions
19. Cook for 1 minute
20. Whisk in broth and juice 
21. Cook for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring continuously, or until the sauce thickens
22. Return pork to pan, turning the pork to coat with the sauce
23. Remove from heat
24. Serve
